The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Virk on Mission World Cup

OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

Kingston: N.S. Virk, the International Cricket Councils regional security officer for India and Sri Lanka, is in the West Indies to make himself familiar with conditions in these parts. 

Im the only one who hasnt ever had an assignment in the West Indies and, because of next years World Cup, it was felt that I make myself familiar with things here, Virk told The Telegraph on Sunday. 

One of five regional security officers, Virk will be around till the end of the ongoing one-day series ? May 28. 

The India-West Indies face-offs are, of course, being monitored by Ron Hope, regional security officer for England and the West Indies. 




